race.comment: OAKFIELD MARS (9) wasn't suited dropping back to 1150m at the Beaumont track last start - overlook that result. Ran on powerfully to be beaten a neck two back over 1300m at Taree which is a strong form reference for this modest maiden. MAXIMUM RIDE (3) struggled in a much stronger maiden at the provincials last time out. Overcame a slow start to just miss the placings the run prior to that over today's trip at Taree. Draws the fence and should be right in the finish. CASTRO (1) picked up nicely in the closing stages to grab third when fresh from a spell over 1318m at this track recently. Lightly raced four-year-old with plenty of scope for improvement. CODONAS (2) backs up nine days after failing over the mile at Parkes. Has placed at today's trip so worth forgiving. BOLD BENDER (7) ran a better race last start. Still a maiden after 33 runs so one for the exotics only.
